5:
Starview, eat your heart out! Now
THIS is a vista! The great weather
sure doesn't hurt, either.
9:
We didn't come here to admire the
view. Besides, Palpebra isn't your
real home, is it?
14:
That's very true! But don't fretâ€”our
destination isn't all that far! We
might have to do a bit of searching
for it, though.
19:
Searching? You mean you don't
know where your own hometown is?
22:
We Sheephirds are a nomadic
people! We constantly change the
location of our settlementsâ€”usually
in the perimeter around Palpebra.
25:
But given how much Palpebra's
been growing lately, even the outer
regions are being cultivated and
settled! The Sheephirds tend to
avoid these areas.
29:
That rubs some people the wrong
way, of course. You get lots of
grumbling about the "good old
days", when we could set up camp
wherever we pleased.
33:
I see... So the Sheephirds lived on
this land long before Palpebra even
existed.
36:
That's right. You Land Walkers only
showed up after the Kaleidoscope
appeared!
41: A shift! And a pretty big one, too.
44:
They're coming more frequently
these days. New layers and routes
are being discovered every
dayâ€”adventurers are ecstatic
about that.
47:
But... it's not all sunshine and roses,
is it? The Kaleidoscope's shifts are...
dangerous.
52:
Maybe... But we can't deny the
benefitsâ€”the population boomed
and advancements in agriculture
allowed us to make starvation a
thing of the past!
55:
It's hard to believe that this area
was a barren wasteland just 50
years ago.
62:
Let's see... It should be somewhere
just around here!
71:
Oh no, you poor thing. Did you get
lost from the herd?
75:
Ah, I get it. You came to us 'cause it's
almost shearing season! Clever girl!
85:
Oh, I just put it together. Is this where
the "Sheep" part in your name
comes from? You're nomadic, so
you herd them around?
90:
Ding-ding-ding! Good guess, Alk.
Though, there's actually another
theory.
92:
First things firstâ€”do you know why
we call you tall folk "Land Walkers"?
96:
Um... Because we... walk on land? I
don't know.
100:
I mean, yes, that's obviously part of
it! But wait, there's moreâ€”
103:
A long time ago, humans were held
captive in a place called the Field of
Sorrow. Then, a guide appeared
before themâ€”he used the light of
the stars to guide them to salvation!
107:
The humans and their guide began
a long journey, all the way to the
farthest ends of the earth. Finally,
they arrived in a vast, golden plain.
110:
In the throes of their jubilation, many
humans knelt before their guideâ€”
"You are our king, now and forever,"
they proclaimed.
114:
Thus the newly formed kingdom
came to be called the Farlands, and
its peopleâ€”who had travelled
immeasurable distancesâ€”Land
Walkers. Or so the story goes.
118:
But, wait... What does that story have
to do with Sheephirds?
121:
That's the twistâ€”apparently the one
who guided their people was one of
OUR ancestors!
129:
It's said that, not only did we show
the Land Walkers the way, but we
also herded the sheep that
sustained them throughout the long
journey! Hence our name.
133:
But there are people out there who
would get real mad if they heard
that storyâ€”I won't be shouting it
from the rooftops anytime soon.
138:
Come on, stories like that get
changed up all the time. It's
probably all a load of bullcrap.
141:
To tell you the truth, I'm inclined to
agree... But there's one more
strange thing about this little legend.
144:
In it, a load of humans appeared out
of nowhere in the Field of Sorrow...
How'd that happen, exactly?
147:
Incidentally, we don't actually call it
the "Field of Sorrow." The place is a
holy site for us, so we use the term
"Land of Beginnings."
152:
A holy site... I see!
Do you think it's possible those
humans came here via the World
Flipper?
156:
I don't know for sure, but I'm
confident the guide brought people
here from another world.
159:
And he used the light of stars to do
so!
165:
Enough talking, thenâ€”let's get a
move on! It'll be faster to just ask the
elder ourselves.
167:
Hehehe. The elder never told me any
of the important stuff worth hearing,
but now that I have you here, she's
sure to spill the beans!
171:
Let's go, Stella.
It can't hurt to hear what they've got
to say. Either way, it won't change
what we have to do.
179:
I... I need to know...
Who I really am.
